  publisher    = {John Wiley \& Sons, Inc.},
  doi          = {10.1002/scj.10359},
  abstract     = {Turbo codes are known as a class of error-correcting
                  codes which have high error-correcting performance
                  with efficient decoding algorithm. Characteristics
                  of the iterative decoding algorithm have been
                  studied in detail through a variety of numerical
                  experiments, but theoretical results are still
                  insufficient. In this paper, this issue is addressed
                  from the information geometrical viewpoint. As a
                  result, a mathematical framework for analyzing turbo
                  codes is obtained, and some of the fundamental
                  properties of turbo decoding are elucidated based on
                  this framework. Recently, it has been pointed out
                  that the turbo decoding algorithm is related to the
                  decoding algorithm of low-density parity check
                  codes, the computation method of Bethe approximation
                  in statistical physics, and the belief propagation
                  algorithm of Bayesian networks. The mathematical
                  framework given in the present paper can also be
                  used to analyze these wide classes of iterative
                  computation methods, and hence represent a new
                  analysis tool.}
}

