                  ($0.3\le z < 0.6$), and high ($0.6 \le z < 0.85$)
                  redshifts, respectively, with an average false
                  detection rate of 0.022 deg$^{-2}$. The estimated
                  redshifts of the detected clusters are
                  systematically lower than the true values by $\Delta
                  z \sim 0.03$ for halos at $z \le 0.4$, but the
                  relative redshift bias is below $0.5$\% for clusters
