                  interferometric array of eight telescopes operating
                  at a wavelength of $\lambda=1.3$mm. The EHT data
                  resolve a compact emission region with intrahour
                  variability. A variety of imaging and modeling
                  analyses all support an image that is dominated by a
                  bright, thick ring with a diameter of 51.8$\pm{2.3}
                  $\uasbib (68\% credible interval). The ring has
                  modest azimuthal brightness asymmetry and a
                  comparatively dim interior. Using a large suite of
                  numerical simulations, we demonstrate that the EHT
                  images of \sgrabib are consistent with the
                  expected appearance of a Kerr black hole with mass
