  abstract     = {Astrophysical black holes are expected to be
                  described by the Kerr metric. This is the only
                  stationary, vacuum, axisymmetric metric, without
                  electromagnetic charge, that satisfies Einstein's
                  equations and does not have pathologies outside of
                  the event horizon. We present new constraints on
                  potential deviations from the Kerr prediction based
                  on 2017 EHT observations of Sagittarius A$^{\ast}$
