                  spectrum of \sgrabib, we conclude that a
                  thermal surface can be ruled out and a fully
                  reflective one is unlikely. We compare our results
                  to the broader landscape of gravitational
                  tests. Together with the bounds found for
                  stellar-mass black holes and the M87 black hole, our
                  observations provide further support that the
                  external spacetimes of all black holes are described
                  by the Kerr metric, independent of their mass.}
