  abstract     = {The Event Horizon Telescope (EHT) has mapped the
                  central compact radio source of the elliptical
                  galaxy M87 at $1.3$ mm with unprecedented angular
                  resolution. Here we consider the physical
                  implications of the asymmetric ring seen in the 2017
                  EHT data. To this end, we construct a large library
