                  holes by the Event Horizon Telescope (EHT) requires
                  predictions of the polarized emission observable by
                  an Earth-based instrument for a particular model of
                  the black hole accretion system. Such predictions
                  are generated by general relativistic radiative
                  transfer (GRRT) codes, which integrate the equations
                  of polarized radiative transfer in curved
                  spacetime. A selection of ray-tracing GRRT codes
                  used within the EHT Collaboration is evaluated for
                  accuracy and consistency in producing a selection of
                  test images, demonstrating that the various methods
